It looks like with relatively few changes you could make `get_variables` an iterator rather than returning a dict. Then do something like
```
for v, vartype, lb, ub in get_variables(parse_output):
    if vartype is Vartype.INTEGER:
        obj.add_variable(vartype, v, lb, ub)
    elif vartype is Vartype.BINARY:
        obj.add_variable(vartype, v)
    else:
        RuntimeError("unexpected vartype")  # or maybe ValueError if this hasn't been checked before
