I think I'd like to have a flexible way to design a tokenization pipeline.  E.g.:

```python
class TokenizerPipeline(Tokenizer):

  def __init__(self, tokenizer, token_processors*):
    self.tokenizer = tokenizer  # start of the pipeline
    self.token_processors = token_processor

  def tokenize(self, text):
    tokens = self.tokenizer.tokenize(text)
    for token_processor in self.token_processors:
      tokens = token_processor.process(tokens)

class TokenProcessor:
  def process(self, tokens):
    raise NotImplementedError()

class CJKSegmenter:
  def process(self, tokens):
    # do the logic of looking for CJK sequences and segmenting them here. 

wikitext_split_w_cjk = TokenizerPipeline(wikitext_split, CJKSegmenter())
```

